WEBVTT

00:00:04.230 --> 00:00:06.250
Good afternoon, dear colleagues.

00:00:06.710 --> 00:00:08.110
I am Oleg Bakstansky, a professor

00:00:08.510 --> 00:00:09.930
at the Plekhanov Russian Academy

00:00:09.930 --> 00:00:11.510
of Economics.

00:00:12.010 --> 00:00:14.230
At the Plekhanov Academy, I teach MBA courses

00:00:14.230 --> 00:00:17.770
on the topics of human resources management,

00:00:17.770 --> 00:00:18.690
organizational management,

00:00:18.690 --> 00:00:20.610
and the sociology of organizations.

00:00:21.210 --> 00:00:24.430
Today we are going to talk about

00:00:24.430 --> 00:00:27.490
the science of organizational behavior.

00:00:28.730 --> 00:00:29.910
To a large extent this is a new discipline,

00:00:29.910 --> 00:00:32.470
everyone has already encountered

00:00:32.470 --> 00:00:35.130
it, and in the day-to-day activities

00:00:35.130 --> 00:00:38.030
of your organisation we do something,

00:00:38.030 --> 00:00:39.330
we undertake something,

00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:40.810
we succeed in something,

00:00:40.810 --> 00:00:43.950
we agree with something, we disagree

00:00:44.010 --> 00:00:44.930
with something.

00:00:44.930 --> 00:00:46.070
This or that production

00:00:46.070 --> 00:00:47.490
conflicts arise, this or that

00:00:47.490 --> 00:00:48.290
action.

00:00:49.050 --> 00:00:50.110
That is, organizational behavior

00:00:50.110 --> 00:00:51.330
is what surrounds us,

00:00:51.350 --> 00:00:53.430
surrounds us in our constant

00:00:53.430 --> 00:00:55.590
daily work activities.

00:00:56.530 --> 00:00:57.710
Naturally, the problem

00:00:57.710 --> 00:00:58.790
of organizational behavior

00:00:59.350 --> 00:01:01.830
is quite an interesting and

00:01:01.830 --> 00:01:03.390
extensive field of study.

00:01:04.430 --> 00:01:07.870
And researchers pay quite a

00:01:07.870 --> 00:01:09.510
lot of attention to this section.

00:01:10.090 --> 00:01:11.610
As always, we can notice that organizational

00:01:11.610 --> 00:01:12.990
behavior as a scientific

00:01:12.990 --> 00:01:15.130
discipline has developed

00:01:15.130 --> 00:01:17.370
abroad.

00:01:17.910 --> 00:01:21.890
And it was only at the end of the

00:01:21.890 --> 00:01:24.670
1990s that it gradually began to

00:01:24.670 --> 00:01:28.450
receive realization, to attract

00:01:28.450 --> 00:01:30.970
interest and to be present in

00:01:30.970 --> 00:01:33.770
studies of domestic specialists,

00:01:33.770 --> 00:01:35.190
or even more accurately,

00:01:35.750 --> 00:01:36.970
domestic employers, firm owners

00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.830
and businessmen came to the conclusion

00:01:40.830 --> 00:01:42.570
that in order to raise the quality

00:01:42.570 --> 00:01:45.550
of business, to improve their

00:01:45.950 --> 00:01:47.470
business indicators and business

00:01:47.470 --> 00:01:49.510
results, it was necessary to

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:52.370
use those developments that already

00:01:52.370 --> 00:01:55.190
exist in this science, in order

00:01:55.190 --> 00:01:58.270
to be able to respond to

00:01:58.270 --> 00:02:00.510
the demands that are placed

00:02:00.510 --> 00:02:03.430
on business, and to have the

00:02:03.430 --> 00:02:04.830
opportunity in some or

00:02:04.830 --> 00:02:07.630
other of the above-mentioned

00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:09.630
fields of study.

00:02:11.950 --> 00:02:14.530
We will study different aspects

00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:16.470
of this discipline later on.

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:19.970
And today we will talk with you about

00:02:19.970 --> 00:02:22.070
how the science of organization,

00:02:22.570 --> 00:02:25.070
as the science of organizational

00:02:25.070 --> 00:02:26.850
behavior, arose, how it has

00:02:26.850 --> 00:02:29.550
developed, what its roots are,

00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:31.470
what its related specialties

00:02:31.470 --> 00:02:32.890
are, what its connections are,

00:02:32.890 --> 00:02:37.130
and, accordingly, what it does

00:02:37.130 --> 00:02:38.670
and what its usefulness is.

00:02:38.810 --> 00:02:40.650
The first question before

00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:42.270
us is, of course, what organizational

00:02:42.730 --> 00:02:43.810
behavior is.

00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:46.790
Here's the definition of the discipline,

00:02:46.850 --> 00:02:47.930
because if we know the definition,

00:02:47.930 --> 00:02:49.210
then it's pretty much

00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:50.170
already clear what

00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.590
this science is going to do.

00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:55.490
As for definitions, there is no

00:02:55.610 --> 00:02:57.190
unambiguous solution here either,

00:02:57.190 --> 00:02:58.750
because there are many different

00:02:58.750 --> 00:03:01.090
approaches, many authoritative

00:03:01.090 --> 00:03:03.030
sources.

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:07.190
And, accordingly, each school sees

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:09.030
and studies the problems of

00:03:09.030 --> 00:03:10.570
organizational behavior in its own way.

00:03:11.350 --> 00:03:13.430
Since our task is to

00:03:13.430 --> 00:03:14.910
get a general idea of what

00:03:14.910 --> 00:03:16.070
organizational behavior

00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:17.070
is, we will not go into

00:03:17.150 --> 00:03:19.950
all sorts of arguments

00:03:19.950 --> 00:03:22.430
about the nuances that

00:03:22.430 --> 00:03:24.070
arise in the study of

00:03:24.070 --> 00:03:26.670
human behavior in organizations.

00:03:27.910 --> 00:03:29.310
We will settle with you

00:03:29.310 --> 00:03:30.790
on a neutral definition, which

00:03:30.790 --> 00:03:32.730
is very general, but at the same

00:03:32.730 --> 00:03:34.390
time it covers all those aspects

00:03:34.390 --> 00:03:36.170
that arise in the study of human

00:03:36.170 --> 00:03:38.850
behavior in an organization.

00:03:39.110 --> 00:03:40.950
And then, as we become

00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:42.350
more familiar with the discipline,

00:03:42.470 --> 00:03:44.290
we will go deeper and deeper into

00:03:44.290 --> 00:03:46.210
it, respectively, and look

00:03:46.210 --> 00:03:47.890
at all sorts of facets that

00:03:47.990 --> 00:03:49.630
arise in this situation.

00:03:50.710 --> 00:03:52.690
So, organizational behavior can

00:03:52.690 --> 00:03:55.270
be defined as a certain area of

00:03:55.270 --> 00:03:58.710
knowledge about how people behave

00:03:59.150 --> 00:04:00.790
while in this or that organization,

00:04:00.790 --> 00:04:03.150
and how the behavior of

00:04:03.150 --> 00:04:05.190
people in this organization

00:04:05.190 --> 00:04:07.150
affects, determines,

00:04:07.390 --> 00:04:09.470
predetermines the results

00:04:09.470 --> 00:04:11.670
of this organization.

00:04:17.510 --> 00:04:17.250
Organizational behavior has

00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:19.630
been considered by many

00:04:19.630 --> 00:04:22.910
studies, but perhaps one of the

00:04:22.910 --> 00:04:24.590
first most authoritative textbooks

00:04:24.590 --> 00:04:25.750
on organizational behavior was

00:04:25.750 --> 00:04:27.930
written by Francis Lutens, and

00:04:27.930 --> 00:04:30.910
accordingly Lutens followed

00:04:31.010 --> 00:04:34.350
a similar definition, in fact

00:04:34.350 --> 00:04:36.110
he was the first to give such

00:04:36.110 --> 00:04:37.910
a definition, and Lutens

00:04:37.910 --> 00:04:41.550
believed that organizational

00:04:41.550 --> 00:04:42.490
behavior is the science of

00:04:42.490 --> 00:04:45.670
describing, explaining, predicting,

00:04:46.250 --> 00:04:48.150
managing human behavior

00:04:48.150 --> 00:04:50.410
in organizations.

00:04:51.630 --> 00:04:53.310
What we need to point out

00:04:53.310 --> 00:04:55.270
right away is that organizational

00:04:55.270 --> 00:04:56.810
behavior is a science.

00:04:57.250 --> 00:04:58.890
Which is inherent in

00:04:58.890 --> 00:05:00.590
its own metalogical apparatus, which

00:05:00.590 --> 00:05:01.970
we will talk to you about next.

00:05:02.470 --> 00:05:03.430
Which is inherent in its

00:05:03.430 --> 00:05:05.030
terminology, which is inherent in

00:05:05.030 --> 00:05:06.010
its tradition.

00:05:06.010 --> 00:05:08.650
And, accordingly, as any scientific

00:05:08.650 --> 00:05:10.950
discipline, organizational

00:05:12.010 --> 00:05:13.290
behavior must describe human

00:05:13.290 --> 00:05:15.950
behavior in an organization,

00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:18.830
explain human behavior in

00:05:18.830 --> 00:05:20.250
an organization.

00:05:20.610 --> 00:05:23.230
That is, to find out

00:05:23.230 --> 00:05:25.150
those regularities, those laws that

00:05:25.150 --> 00:05:27.110
govern that behavior, and to

00:05:27.110 --> 00:05:30.110
predict how the person will behave

00:05:30.110 --> 00:05:31.510
later in the organization,

00:05:31.510 --> 00:05:33.350
how he will fit into the role,

00:05:33.350 --> 00:05:36.110
into the mission of that organization,

00:05:36.110 --> 00:05:37.330
how he will contribute

00:05:37.330 --> 00:05:38.470
to the fulfillment of certain

00:05:38.470 --> 00:05:39.610
tasks, what he will do

00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:40.530
in the organization.

00:05:40.530 --> 00:05:43.050
Will he really be that necessary

00:05:43.050 --> 00:05:44.270
part, that necessary

00:05:44.270 --> 00:05:45.410
element that will contribute

00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:49.230
to the objectives of

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:50.890
the company.

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:52.650
Either he will be engaged in

00:05:52.650 --> 00:05:54.770
either sabotage or he will

00:05:54.770 --> 00:05:56.850
be neutral to the functional

00:05:56.850 --> 00:05:57.730
responsibilities that are

00:05:57.830 --> 00:05:59.530
entrusted to him.

00:06:00.010 --> 00:06:01.750
It's essentially the same loyalty

00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:05.530
problem that you have in a commercial

00:06:05.530 --> 00:06:08.370
organization all the time.

00:06:08.950 --> 00:06:11.770
So now let's try to look at

00:06:11.770 --> 00:06:14.630
what disciplines of organizational

00:06:14.630 --> 00:06:17.070
behavior interact with,

00:06:17.070 --> 00:06:18.950
what results it uses, and,

00:06:18.950 --> 00:06:22.270
accordingly, what general

00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:26.250
principles, general

00:06:26.250 --> 00:06:27.650
ideas, general concepts

00:06:27.650 --> 00:06:29.270
it applies.

00:06:32.590 --> 00:06:35.230
If we look at the totality

00:06:35.230 --> 00:06:37.630
of social sciences, which are

00:06:37.770 --> 00:06:39.070
to some extent related to human

00:06:39.070 --> 00:06:41.170
behavior in an organization,

00:06:41.170 --> 00:06:43.630
then first of all, of course,

00:06:43.910 --> 00:06:44.890
we can single out the so-

00:06:44.890 --> 00:06:46.350
called social sciences, social

00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:49.030
disciplines, which study

00:06:49.030 --> 00:06:52.430
how the social environment,

00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:54.710
society, society affects

00:06:54.850 --> 00:06:56.750
the individual, determines

00:06:56.890 --> 00:06:58.030
his behavior.

00:06:58.090 --> 00:07:00.530
Among the social sciences that

00:07:00.530 --> 00:07:01.730
we can see on the slide, first

00:07:02.670 --> 00:07:04.710
of all, of course, general

00:07:04.710 --> 00:07:06.370
psychology can be mentioned

00:07:06.370 --> 00:07:08.770
because in any organization,

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:10.890
there are always living people

00:07:10.890 --> 00:07:14.010
with their emotions, their

00:07:14.010 --> 00:07:16.010
cognitive cognitive mechanisms,

00:07:16.010 --> 00:07:19.030
their affects, conflicts,

00:07:19.550 --> 00:07:22.630
aggression, various

00:07:22.630 --> 00:07:27.390
desires, various feelings.

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:28.230


00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:31.150
And as far as the human being is

00:07:31.150 --> 00:07:33.870
concerned, every living person is first

00:07:33.870 --> 00:07:37.210
of all a certain subjective formation.

00:07:38.530 --> 00:07:40.730
He thinks first of all not about his

00:07:40.730 --> 00:07:42.650
work, but about the problems that

00:07:42.650 --> 00:07:44.790
surround him, about the tasks

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:46.450
he needs to solve.

00:07:46.730 --> 00:07:48.210
He thinks about the fact that he has quarreled

00:07:48.310 --> 00:07:50.050
with someone, that he has quarreled with

00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:53.150
someone, that he needs to pay back certain

00:07:53.150 --> 00:07:55.710
debts, to do certain things.

00:07:56.610 --> 00:07:59.110
And in this connection, his work

00:07:59.110 --> 00:08:02.070
is only one part of his life.

00:08:02.830 --> 00:08:04.870
This is why quite a lot of material has

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:06.450
already been accumulated in psychology,

00:08:06.610 --> 00:08:09.990
which makes it possible to analyze and

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:13.230
understand different aspects of human behavior.

00:08:13.590 --> 00:08:15.570
And, of course, organizational

00:08:15.570 --> 00:08:18.450
behavior to a very large extent,

00:08:18.450 --> 00:08:20.990
takes results from the

00:08:20.990 --> 00:08:22.590
economics that exists in general

00:08:22.590 --> 00:08:24.230
psychology.

00:08:24.590 --> 00:08:26.130
But at the same time, it should

00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:28.490
be noted that psychology itself

00:08:28.490 --> 00:08:32.030
is a vast science, and it will

00:08:32.030 --> 00:08:34.790
concentrate its attention on

00:08:34.790 --> 00:08:37.190
different kinds of human activity

00:08:37.190 --> 00:08:38.470
and behavior.

00:08:39.330 --> 00:08:41.450
Psychology highlights such a large

00:08:41.450 --> 00:08:43.130
section as social psychology.

00:08:43.450 --> 00:08:44.670
What is social psychology

00:08:44.670 --> 00:08:46.370
is a discipline that studies

00:08:46.370 --> 00:08:48.630
human behavior in society, how

00:08:48.630 --> 00:08:52.330
the human environment affects

00:08:52.330 --> 00:08:54.870
individual human behavior, and

00:08:54.870 --> 00:08:57.730
how a person changes the behavior

00:08:57.730 --> 00:08:59.850
of the group in which

00:08:59.850 --> 00:09:00.870
they are in.

00:09:02.710 --> 00:09:05.130
What concerns social psychology,

00:09:05.130 --> 00:09:08.410
this discipline has been around

00:09:08.410 --> 00:09:10.050
for about two centuries,

00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:12.610
and here again there are various

00:09:12.610 --> 00:09:15.090
kinds of patterns, approaches

00:09:15.090 --> 00:09:17.950
that allow us to describe

00:09:17.950 --> 00:09:20.210
to some degree both human

00:09:20.210 --> 00:09:22.850
behavior and the impact

00:09:22.850 --> 00:09:25.630
of other people

00:09:25.630 --> 00:09:28.070
on a person.

00:09:28.590 --> 00:09:31.230
To understand what social roles

00:09:31.230 --> 00:09:34.950
a person performs as a husband, a

00:09:37.610 --> 00:09:39.870
boss, a subordinate, what social

00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:41.990
functions he performs, what social

00:09:41.990 --> 00:09:44.290
expectations are placed on him, what

00:09:45.670 --> 00:09:48.570
social roles he can play, and

00:09:48.570 --> 00:09:50.310
why a person seeks to occupy these

00:09:50.310 --> 00:09:51.910
or those social roles, what

00:09:51.910 --> 00:09:53.970
opportunities they give him.

00:09:54.930 --> 00:09:58.330
And in this regard just this is a very

00:09:58.330 --> 00:09:59.390
important section of the

00:09:59.390 --> 00:10:01.230
same organizational behavior, because

00:10:01.230 --> 00:10:03.850
what is a person's behavior in an organization?

00:10:04.650 --> 00:10:07.890
We spend at least one third of

00:10:07.890 --> 00:10:09.550
our lives at work.

00:10:10.570 --> 00:10:12.710
And in this connection we

00:10:12.710 --> 00:10:14.270
go to work not only to receive

00:10:14.270 --> 00:10:16.890
money and provide our comfortable

00:10:16.890 --> 00:10:19.630
life in the surrounding

00:10:19.630 --> 00:10:20.610
society.

00:10:21.010 --> 00:10:22.230
We go to work to gain prestige,

00:10:22.230 --> 00:10:25.370
to win the attention

00:10:25.370 --> 00:10:27.370
of others.

00:10:27.690 --> 00:10:29.330
We go to work in order to build

00:10:29.330 --> 00:10:31.770
a certain career ladder, we set

00:10:31.770 --> 00:10:34.270
ourselves certain limits in order

00:10:34.270 --> 00:10:38.230
to receive a new assignment,

00:10:38.230 --> 00:10:41.350
in order to realize ourselves,

00:10:41.350 --> 00:10:45.410
to find our field of applicability,

00:10:45.410 --> 00:10:46.870
to realize certain

00:10:46.870 --> 00:10:48.070
abilities.

00:10:48.650 --> 00:10:51.350
Each of you who have come today

00:10:51.350 --> 00:10:54.770
to hear about organizational

00:10:54.770 --> 00:10:55.770
behavior has enough of your

00:10:56.190 --> 00:10:58.770
own experience of working in

00:10:58.770 --> 00:11:00.870
different organizations.

00:11:01.110 --> 00:11:02.550
He knows perfectly well what he wants, how

00:11:02.630 --> 00:11:03.150
he wants it.

00:11:03.150 --> 00:11:05.770
But nevertheless, you want to

00:11:05.770 --> 00:11:07.110
acquire new knowledge.

00:11:07.330 --> 00:11:09.330
Again, knowing that this

00:11:09.330 --> 00:11:12.250
new knowledge, new skills

00:11:12.250 --> 00:11:13.210
will go a long way toward

00:11:13.210 --> 00:11:16.870
making you more successful,

00:11:16.870 --> 00:11:19.530
more empowered at your

00:11:19.530 --> 00:11:23.110
job, more successful at

00:11:23.110 --> 00:11:24.510
the functional tasks

00:11:24.510 --> 00:11:25.790
that you face.

00:11:26.070 --> 00:11:27.550
Tasks of management, tasks

00:11:27.550 --> 00:11:30.670
of functioning, tasks of solving

00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:33.870
these or those issues related

00:11:33.870 --> 00:11:35.250
to your daily activities.

00:11:36.110 --> 00:11:37.410
And accordingly, again, each

00:11:37.770 --> 00:11:40.050
of you wants further career growth,

00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:41.510
further promotion, because this,

00:11:41.510 --> 00:11:43.810
on the one hand, is an increase

00:11:43.810 --> 00:11:47.990
of your welfare, on the other

00:11:47.990 --> 00:11:50.370
hand, this is an assessment

00:11:50.750 --> 00:11:52.570
of the achievements that

00:11:52.710 --> 00:11:53.450
you have made.

00:11:54.230 --> 00:11:56.810
Any person is very much interested

00:11:56.810 --> 00:11:59.250
in the fact that those actions that

00:11:59.250 --> 00:12:01.670
he does, will be appreciated.

00:12:02.410 --> 00:12:05.410
Because if we do something and

00:12:05.610 --> 00:12:07.810
we don't get appropriate feedback,

00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:10.070
we lose motivation in that

00:12:10.070 --> 00:12:10.790
regard.

00:12:10.790 --> 00:12:12.330
Why do we need to do

00:12:12.330 --> 00:12:13.710
something and make this or that

00:12:13.710 --> 00:12:15.610
effort if no one notices it

00:12:15.610 --> 00:12:16.270
anyway?

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:18.610
This whole area of activity is

00:12:18.610 --> 00:12:19.970
what is being studied,

00:12:20.090 --> 00:12:21.210
analyzed, considered in social

00:12:21.210 --> 00:12:23.310
psychology, and the relevant

00:12:23.310 --> 00:12:26.710
knowledge is very much in

00:12:26.710 --> 00:12:29.020
demand with regard to the

00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:30.330
analysis and study of organizational

00:12:30.330 --> 00:12:31.650
behavior.

00:12:33.150 --> 00:12:34.750
In addition to social psychology,

00:12:35.210 --> 00:12:37.130
psychology also deals with

00:12:37.130 --> 00:12:40.750
such a section as work

00:12:40.750 --> 00:12:41.810
psychology.

00:12:42.690 --> 00:12:43.650
It has different names.

00:12:43.890 --> 00:12:45.210
Engineering psychology,

00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:46.830
environmental psychology,

00:12:46.970 --> 00:12:49.070
industrial-organizational psychology.

00:12:49.590 --> 00:12:51.130
It all depends on tradition.

00:12:51.950 --> 00:12:53.290
In Russian tradition, this is

00:12:53.290 --> 00:12:54.430
labor psychology.

00:12:54.530 --> 00:12:55.770
In the foreign tradition, there is no

00:12:55.770 --> 00:12:56.890
such concept.

00:12:56.890 --> 00:12:59.250
Then all of the issues that are addressed

00:12:59.250 --> 00:13:01.430
by this discipline fall under the

00:13:01.430 --> 00:13:01.770
category

00:13:01.770 --> 00:13:03.570
of industrial-organizational psychology.

00:13:04.510 --> 00:13:07.210
How a person works, what

00:13:07.210 --> 00:13:09.730
conditions contribute to the

00:13:09.730 --> 00:13:12.490
quality of his work, what conditions

00:13:12.490 --> 00:13:14.410
have a negative impact on

00:13:14.410 --> 00:13:17.250
this work, how to furnish

00:13:17.250 --> 00:13:19.150
the workplace for a person to

00:13:19.250 --> 00:13:22.190
be successful in its functions,

00:13:22.190 --> 00:13:24.890
what helps and what hinders,

00:13:25.010 --> 00:13:27.010
how to arrange the tables?

00:13:27.110 --> 00:13:28.390
What distance should a person have

00:13:28.390 --> 00:13:29.450
from the computer?

00:13:30.770 --> 00:13:32.350
How many people can be in

00:13:32.350 --> 00:13:33.230
one room?

00:13:34.030 --> 00:13:36.330
How do you favorably arrange people?

00:13:36.510 --> 00:13:38.070
Everyone has his own isolated

00:13:38.070 --> 00:13:40.610
room, or a modern office

00:13:40.610 --> 00:13:43.650
style, when everyone is in sight

00:13:43.650 --> 00:13:44.590
of each other.

00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:46.770
There are pros, there are cons.

00:13:47.230 --> 00:13:48.790
And these are all issues

00:13:48.790 --> 00:13:51.590
that are considered

00:13:51.590 --> 00:13:53.770
in work psychology,

00:13:53.770 --> 00:13:55.990
because they greatly

00:13:55.990 --> 00:13:59.070
influence and affect the

00:13:59.070 --> 00:14:02.970
results that arise from

00:14:02.970 --> 00:14:05.350
your functioning.

00:14:06.930 --> 00:14:10.890
Beyond that, of great importance in

00:14:10.890 --> 00:14:13.110
human relations psychology, and of

00:14:13.110 --> 00:14:15.250
course, of great importance to a

00:14:15.250 --> 00:14:16.790
proper understanding of organizational

00:14:16.790 --> 00:14:18.850
behavior, is the ethics of

00:14:18.850 --> 00:14:20.110
relationships.

00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:22.510
People interact with each

00:14:22.510 --> 00:14:23.430
other, and they interact

00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:24.590
with each other according

00:14:24.590 --> 00:14:25.470
to certain rules.

00:14:26.450 --> 00:14:29.290
There are written rules, various

00:14:29.290 --> 00:14:32.890
kinds of laws, requirements,

00:14:32.970 --> 00:14:34.330
instructions which are prescribed,

00:14:34.330 --> 00:14:35.270
which we read, which

00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:37.330
we get acquainted with, sign for.

00:14:37.830 --> 00:14:39.490
There are unwritten rules.

00:14:39.810 --> 00:14:41.150
And unwritten, so-called

00:14:41.150 --> 00:14:42.490
informal norms of communication

00:14:42.490 --> 00:14:45.390
often play a much more important

00:14:45.390 --> 00:14:47.830
role than written ones.

00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:50.110
For informal relationships, this

00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:51.250
is the relationship that arises

00:14:51.250 --> 00:14:52.930
in the team between people.

00:14:53.190 --> 00:14:57.130
After all, spending 8-10-12 hours

00:14:57.130 --> 00:15:01.450
at work, who knows how, we are

00:15:01.450 --> 00:15:02.630
not spending this time in

00:15:02.630 --> 00:15:04.730
a vacuum, we are interacting

00:15:04.730 --> 00:15:07.710
with other people, we are giving

00:15:07.710 --> 00:15:10.550
them orders, we are getting the

00:15:10.550 --> 00:15:12.250
information we need for

00:15:12.250 --> 00:15:13.330
our future work.

00:15:14.170 --> 00:15:16.030
And in this context it's

00:15:16.030 --> 00:15:18.330
very important to build a relationship

00:15:18.330 --> 00:15:22.570
with these people, how easy

00:15:22.570 --> 00:15:24.510
and fast you will get the data

00:15:24.510 --> 00:15:27.470
you need, how complete

00:15:27.470 --> 00:15:30.070
the data will be, how formal

00:15:30.070 --> 00:15:31.710
the data will be.

00:15:31.790 --> 00:15:33.470
It all depends on what kind of

00:15:33.470 --> 00:15:34.810
informal contacts, informal relationships

00:15:34.810 --> 00:15:36.390
we have in place.

00:15:36.850 --> 00:15:39.970
This is something that belongs

00:15:39.970 --> 00:15:46.010
to the field of ethics, and usually

00:15:46.010 --> 00:15:50.170
we don't pay much attention to

00:15:50.410 --> 00:15:53.070
it, we very rarely focus our

00:15:53.070 --> 00:15:54.950
thought on how we treat

00:15:54.950 --> 00:15:56.770
others, how others treat us.

00:15:56.950 --> 00:15:58.670
We usually take it for granted.

00:15:59.110 --> 00:16:01.490
But nevertheless, it is worth noting

00:16:01.610 --> 00:16:05.090
that here is the ethnic gradation

00:16:05.090 --> 00:16:07.130
of relationships, it is the essential

00:16:07.130 --> 00:16:08.510
point that either contributes

00:16:08.510 --> 00:16:11.210
to the fact that we are happy

00:16:11.210 --> 00:16:12.250
to come to work, or largely

00:16:12.250 --> 00:16:13.830
hinders our performance, our

00:16:14.290 --> 00:16:17.730
work, let us say, we do

00:16:17.890 --> 00:16:20.670
not want to go to work in

00:16:20.670 --> 00:16:22.510
the morning, and we go there

00:16:22.510 --> 00:16:23.850
because we have to.

00:16:23.970 --> 00:16:25.470
And naturally, we need to

00:16:25.470 --> 00:16:27.570
hurry to finish our work hours

00:16:27.570 --> 00:16:29.970
and leave the collective, the

00:16:29.970 --> 00:16:32.570
society where we don't like to be.

00:16:32.890 --> 00:16:34.390
Naturally, this attitude

00:16:34.390 --> 00:16:36.730
has a rather negative

00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:37.950
impact on the results

00:16:38.030 --> 00:16:39.870
that we get.

00:16:39.870 --> 00:16:42.030
Very close to this row of

00:16:42.030 --> 00:16:44.830
attitudes is such a discipline as

00:16:45.030 --> 00:16:45.810
cultural studies.

00:16:46.110 --> 00:16:47.410
Of course, ethics and cultural

00:16:47.410 --> 00:16:48.890
studies are quite related, because

00:16:48.890 --> 00:16:51.470
cultural studies are those or

00:16:51.470 --> 00:16:53.450
other cultural norms that we

00:16:53.450 --> 00:16:54.250
carry out.

00:16:54.690 --> 00:16:57.450
But then again, you can go to work

00:16:57.450 --> 00:16:58.330
in different ways.

00:16:58.650 --> 00:17:01.790
If it's hot outside, you can

00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:03.690
come to work in a T-shirt, in shorts.

00:17:04.230 --> 00:17:06.250
But this, of course, will

00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:09.570
to a large extent not coincide

00:17:09.570 --> 00:17:11.410
with those or other corporate

00:17:11.410 --> 00:17:15.050
norms of behaviour, ways

00:17:15.050 --> 00:17:17.110
of behaving, corporate perceptions.

00:17:18.570 --> 00:17:20.850
Corporate perceptions are also

00:17:20.850 --> 00:17:23.070
the embodiment of a certain

00:17:23.070 --> 00:17:24.250
social culture.

00:17:25.210 --> 00:17:27.170
If you work in a bank, if you work for

00:17:27.170 --> 00:17:29.030
a prestigious insurance company,

00:17:29.030 --> 00:17:30.450
they have their own style of dress

00:17:30.450 --> 00:17:31.670
which you have to follow

00:17:31.670 --> 00:17:33.390
regardless of whether it's convenient

00:17:33.390 --> 00:17:35.230
or uncomfortable for you.

00:17:35.230 --> 00:17:38.570
But there are certain norms

00:17:38.570 --> 00:17:39.910
and you have to follow

00:17:39.910 --> 00:17:41.370
these norms, it is useless

00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:43.810
to ask why they are like that.

00:17:43.810 --> 00:17:45.550
They are like that because

00:17:45.550 --> 00:17:49.310
in this organization they are,

00:17:49.310 --> 00:17:51.550
and if you want to be in this

00:17:51.550 --> 00:17:53.110
organization, if you want to

00:17:53.110 --> 00:17:54.570
develop in this organization,

00:17:54.570 --> 00:17:59.230
if you want your career prospects

00:17:59.230 --> 00:18:01.590
to grow in this organization,

00:18:01.590 --> 00:18:03.690
you have to accept the culture

00:18:03.910 --> 00:18:05.330
that is in this organization,

00:18:05.510 --> 00:18:07.590
and not try to change

00:18:07.590 --> 00:18:09.110
it.

00:18:09.770 --> 00:18:11.610
The culture is built up over

00:18:11.610 --> 00:18:15.090
a long period of time, and it's

00:18:15.090 --> 00:18:17.690
not easy to change, either.

00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:19.550
It's quite a bone structure.

00:18:19.810 --> 00:18:21.170
People change, bosses change,

00:18:21.170 --> 00:18:23.150
the buildings where the same organization

00:18:23.150 --> 00:18:24.610
is located change, but the people

00:18:24.790 --> 00:18:25.990
who work in that organization

00:18:25.990 --> 00:18:26.870
remain.

00:18:27.090 --> 00:18:28.710
And these people, they are the

00:18:28.710 --> 00:18:30.690
carriers of those beloved cultural norms.

00:18:32.190 --> 00:18:34.730
In terms of the social sciences,

00:18:34.730 --> 00:18:36.950
we have looked at such elements

00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:38.210
as general psychology, social

00:18:38.310 --> 00:18:39.910
psychology, work psychology,

00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:41.290
ethico-culturalism.

00:18:41.850 --> 00:18:44.250
Naturally, we could also

00:18:44.250 --> 00:18:46.230
talk about other social disciplines,

00:18:46.230 --> 00:18:49.650
but it so happens that it is these

00:18:49.650 --> 00:18:54.710
approaches that have the most

00:18:54.710 --> 00:18:56.410
significant impact on organizational

00:18:56.410 --> 00:18:57.650
behavior.

00:18:58.450 --> 00:19:02.090
It is these disciplines that have accumulated

00:19:02.090 --> 00:19:03.690
the necessary volume of facts,

00:19:03.790 --> 00:19:05.110
the necessary regularities that

00:19:05.450 --> 00:19:08.050
are used in the analysis of organizational

00:19:08.050 --> 00:19:09.670
behavior and prove useful

00:19:09.670 --> 00:19:11.590
for its understanding, for its

00:19:11.590 --> 00:19:13.650
changes, for its correction, for

00:19:13.770 --> 00:19:14.930
its modification.

00:19:16.210 --> 00:19:18.510
This is what concerns the social

00:19:18.510 --> 00:19:20.730
disciplines that are directly

00:19:20.730 --> 00:19:23.530
related to organizational behavior.

00:19:25.110 --> 00:19:27.970
Another discipline that also

00:19:27.970 --> 00:19:29.390
has an impact on organizational

00:19:29.390 --> 00:19:30.130
behavior is management

00:19:30.290 --> 00:19:31.890
psychology.

00:19:32.610 --> 00:19:34.050
Here is what concerns management psychology,

00:19:34.050 --> 00:19:37.410
in fact, of course, it also belongs

00:19:37.630 --> 00:19:38.730
to psychology, but because

00:19:38.730 --> 00:19:40.490
of its importance, because

00:19:40.490 --> 00:19:42.170
of its importance, because of its

00:19:42.250 --> 00:19:43.790
tradition, it is singled out as

00:19:43.790 --> 00:19:46.350
a separate direction, because any

00:19:46.350 --> 00:19:49.030
organization is first of all

00:19:49.030 --> 00:19:50.130
a hierarchy.

00:19:50.310 --> 00:19:53.170
It is a hierarchy, in which there are different

00:19:53.170 --> 00:19:57.030
levels of approaches, different levels

00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.170
of connections.

00:19:58.510 --> 00:20:00.010
Connections of one level are

00:20:00.010 --> 00:20:01.890
horizontal hierarchy, connections of different

00:20:01.890 --> 00:20:03.650
levels are vertical hierarchy, connections

00:20:03.650 --> 00:20:06.690
of subordination, connections of management.

00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:12.490
And since the entire organization

00:20:12.490 --> 00:20:15.290
is people, this structure is

00:20:15.290 --> 00:20:16.590
primarily held together by

00:20:16.590 --> 00:20:18.170
psychological relationships.

00:20:19.950 --> 00:20:21.550
So the discipline of management

00:20:21.550 --> 00:20:23.310
psychology is a very important element

00:20:23.310 --> 00:20:24.710
that is studied in many courses,

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:26.110
including MBI courses, and,

00:20:26.110 --> 00:20:29.350
accordingly, when we talk about

00:20:29.450 --> 00:20:30.550
organizational behavior,

00:20:30.550 --> 00:20:32.230
it is very important for

00:20:32.230 --> 00:20:35.030
us to keep in mind those

00:20:35.030 --> 00:20:36.330
patterns that work on organizational

00:20:36.330 --> 00:20:37.290
management.

00:20:37.770 --> 00:20:39.190
How management is done, whether it's

00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:41.990
authoritarian, and, accordingly, it doesn't

00:20:42.330 --> 00:20:44.570
matter what you think, it doesn't matter

00:20:44.670 --> 00:20:45.630
what you think.

00:20:46.510 --> 00:20:48.610
You have been told what to do and how

00:20:48.610 --> 00:20:50.410
to do it, and your initiative is irrelevant here.

00:20:50.490 --> 00:20:52.330
You have to do what you are told.

00:20:52.570 --> 00:20:53.350
That's one approach.

00:20:54.610 --> 00:20:57.430
And these are approaches that

00:20:57.430 --> 00:21:00.050
exist, including in many successful

00:21:00.050 --> 00:21:01.630
organizations.

00:21:01.750 --> 00:21:02.810
Moreover, with regard

00:21:02.810 --> 00:21:05.510
to the authoritarian approach,

00:21:05.510 --> 00:21:07.170
this is the approach that is

00:21:07.170 --> 00:21:10.530
often very present in domestic

00:21:10.530 --> 00:21:11.570
organizations.

00:21:11.750 --> 00:21:13.490
And later on, we will talk about

00:21:13.490 --> 00:21:14.770
this again in more detail.

00:21:14.990 --> 00:21:16.330
There are other types of

00:21:16.330 --> 00:21:19.250
management which take into account

00:21:19.250 --> 00:21:22.370
your interests, your initiative.

00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:25.010
Moreover, tasks are set for you, and

00:21:25.290 --> 00:21:27.130
then you start to solve this task.

00:21:27.430 --> 00:21:29.110
And you are not told how

00:21:29.210 --> 00:21:30.610
to solve it.

00:21:31.670 --> 00:21:34.310
This is your choice, your capabilities.

00:21:34.630 --> 00:21:36.230
This also belongs to a democratic

00:21:36.230 --> 00:21:37.590
style of management which

00:21:37.590 --> 00:21:41.290
also delegates the

00:21:41.290 --> 00:21:43.030
responsibility for various

00:21:43.030 --> 00:21:44.610
acts you perform.

00:21:44.970 --> 00:21:47.670
There are other styles of management.

00:21:48.670 --> 00:21:50.570
And, as you understand, naturally,

00:21:50.670 --> 00:21:52.410
organizational behavior will

00:21:52.410 --> 00:21:54.690
be largely determined

00:21:54.690 --> 00:21:56.270
by that management style,

00:21:56.270 --> 00:21:58.030
by those psychological patterns

00:21:58.030 --> 00:22:00.230
that will be present in terms

00:22:00.230 --> 00:22:01.230
of management, that

00:22:01.230 --> 00:22:03.270
are present in this organization,

00:22:03.270 --> 00:22:06.370
and it is the psychological

00:22:06.370 --> 00:22:08.030
basis of management that will

00:22:08.030 --> 00:22:09.990
largely shape the organizational

00:22:09.990 --> 00:22:12.630
behavior that exists

00:22:12.630 --> 00:22:16.230
in the organization.

00:22:17.290 --> 00:22:19.350
In any organization there

00:22:19.350 --> 00:22:22.090
are the managers, the top

00:22:22.090 --> 00:22:25.510
managers and the managed, those

00:22:25.510 --> 00:22:28.190
own executives who work in that

00:22:28.190 --> 00:22:29.970
organization, who have their

00:22:30.350 --> 00:22:32.590
own section of executive

00:22:32.590 --> 00:22:35.130
activity and who are responsible

00:22:35.130 --> 00:22:36.710
for that section.

00:22:38.330 --> 00:22:41.110
Naturally, these people, ordinary

00:22:41.110 --> 00:22:42.890
employees, line workers, have

00:22:43.430 --> 00:22:45.610
little chance, little

00:22:45.610 --> 00:22:48.050
opportunity to influence

00:22:48.050 --> 00:22:50.750
the entire organization

00:22:50.750 --> 00:22:53.010
as such, simply because

00:22:53.010 --> 00:22:54.970
their field of activity

00:22:54.970 --> 00:22:56.530
is a very small area.

00:22:57.090 --> 00:22:59.290
And so they are embedded here in this

00:22:59.290 --> 00:23:00.850
system of hierarchy in the structures,

00:23:00.950 --> 00:23:01.910
hierarchies that exist in the organization,

00:23:03.930 --> 00:23:06.790
And they perform only those actions that

00:23:06.790 --> 00:23:11.970
are required to be performed according

00:23:12.050 --> 00:23:13.450
to the business plan of the company,

00:23:13.450 --> 00:23:15.690
according to the organizational

00:23:15.690 --> 00:23:16.750
structure of the company,

00:23:16.750 --> 00:23:18.610
according to that management

00:23:18.610 --> 00:23:21.310
style that exists in the company.

00:23:21.370 --> 00:23:23.690
In this regard, in addition to management

00:23:23.690 --> 00:23:25.750
psychology, a discipline such as sociology

00:23:25.750 --> 00:23:27.250
of organization is of great

00:23:27.250 --> 00:23:31.410
importance for analyzing organizational

00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:33.550
behavior, for its understanding,

00:23:33.550 --> 00:23:35.630
for its systematization.

00:23:36.550 --> 00:23:39.310
Sociology is a science that deals

00:23:39.310 --> 00:23:42.290
with the analysis of the social

00:23:42.290 --> 00:23:44.330
aspects of human behavior.

00:23:44.850 --> 00:23:47.150
But this is no longer an analysis of human

00:23:47.150 --> 00:23:48.110
behavior as psychology, subjective

00:23:48.250 --> 00:23:51.670
analyses of a person's desires,

00:23:51.670 --> 00:23:55.330
motives, emotions, that is, what comes

00:23:55.330 --> 00:23:57.310
from the individual.

00:23:57.370 --> 00:23:59.950
Sociology comes from the group

00:23:59.950 --> 00:24:01.450
a person is in, and, in fact, sociology

00:24:01.450 --> 00:24:03.330
studies those tasks, patterns,

00:24:03.330 --> 00:24:06.450
requirements that

00:24:06.590 --> 00:24:08.790
the group places on the

00:24:08.790 --> 00:24:09.790
individual.

00:24:10.170 --> 00:24:11.290
Sociology is not interested, unlike

00:24:11.290 --> 00:24:13.430
psychology, in what you think about

00:24:13.430 --> 00:24:16.150
the organization, what your emotions

00:24:16.150 --> 00:24:17.610
are, what your experiences are.

00:24:17.730 --> 00:24:18.950
Sociology is only interested

00:24:18.950 --> 00:24:23.670
in the external, or what are called

00:24:23.670 --> 00:24:24.890
objective regularities

00:24:24.890 --> 00:24:27.730
that the organization you

00:24:27.730 --> 00:24:29.710
find yourself in imposes

00:24:29.710 --> 00:24:30.570
on you.

00:24:31.190 --> 00:24:33.850
In the later parts of our course,

00:24:33.850 --> 00:24:34.930
we'll just be looking

00:24:34.930 --> 00:24:36.530
at research methodology,

00:24:36.530 --> 00:24:38.090
and psychological approaches,

00:24:38.090 --> 00:24:39.730
and sociological approaches.

00:24:40.050 --> 00:24:42.650
For now, it is important for us to understand

00:24:42.650 --> 00:24:45.310
this very difference, that the sociology

00:24:45.310 --> 00:24:47.070
of an organization is essentially

00:24:47.310 --> 00:24:49.610
a list of the rigid requirements that

00:24:50.090 --> 00:24:52.050
the organization imposes on you as

00:24:52.050 --> 00:24:53.730
a member of that organization.

00:24:54.770 --> 00:24:56.370
You chose the organization, you

00:24:56.370 --> 00:24:58.290
came to work for it, but since

00:24:58.290 --> 00:25:00.390
you chose it, you have to obey

00:25:00.390 --> 00:25:02.170
those patterns, those corporate

00:25:02.170 --> 00:25:04.070
ethics, that corporate culture,

00:25:04.490 --> 00:25:06.390
those corporate norms, that

00:25:06.390 --> 00:25:08.090
corporate hierarchy that exists

00:25:08.090 --> 00:25:09.730
in that organization.

00:25:11.010 --> 00:25:14.270
And consequently, depending on how

00:25:14.270 --> 00:25:16.250
these relations are built,

00:25:16.250 --> 00:25:20.130
the norms of organizational behavior

00:25:20.130 --> 00:25:23.130
will change, the freedom of

00:25:23.130 --> 00:25:25.430
those actions that you are allowed

00:25:25.530 --> 00:25:29.110
to take, the degree of activity

00:25:29.110 --> 00:25:30.490
that you are allowed to

00:25:30.490 --> 00:25:31.430
be involved in.

