01:07:06.060 --> 01:07:07.240
give different orders.

01:07:07.740 --> 01:07:10.560
And that will introduce a certain amount of confusion.

01:07:10.560 --> 01:07:12.560
I'll always cite, that boss

01:07:12.560 --> 01:07:14.440
told me to do this, and you told me

01:07:14.440 --> 01:07:15.360
to do the other thing now,

01:07:15.360 --> 01:07:17.480
so you figure out amongst yourselves

01:07:17.480 --> 01:07:19.480
who's going to do what.

01:07:19.880 --> 01:07:21.060
I got the instruction, I did.

01:07:22.100 --> 01:07:24.000
Well, which instruction was more important,

01:07:24.680 --> 01:07:26.420
that's not my problem, as they say.

01:07:27.040 --> 01:07:28.500
The commands come from the top.

01:07:28.820 --> 01:07:30.560
And in this way it turned out that

01:07:30.560 --> 01:07:35.040
the worker was not interested in improvement,

01:07:35.040 --> 01:07:37.560
in optimization of work and labor.

01:07:39.960 --> 01:07:42.120
And another important

01:07:42.120 --> 01:07:43.040
element of the classical

01:07:43.040 --> 01:07:45.800
model of organizational

01:07:45.800 --> 01:07:48.840
behavior was the so-called range

01:07:48.840 --> 01:07:49.940
of control.

01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:53.160
There was a limited number of

01:07:53.160 --> 01:07:55.960
subordinates of a given leader.

01:07:56.880 --> 01:07:58.760
And, accordingly, even if the actions

01:07:58.760 --> 01:08:00.340
of those subordinates overlapped

01:08:00.340 --> 01:08:03.100
with the actions of other workers, you,

01:08:03.100 --> 01:08:06.060
as the leader of those particular

01:08:06.060 --> 01:08:07.640
subordinates, had no right to interfere

01:08:07.640 --> 01:08:09.780
with the work of those who were

01:08:09.920 --> 01:08:11.560
not within your sphere of influence.

01:08:12.260 --> 01:08:15.060
It was a rigid mechanical model.

01:08:15.420 --> 01:08:17.640
One leader, this leader's subordinates,

01:08:17.640 --> 01:08:20.560
a rigidly circumscribed sphere

01:08:20.560 --> 01:08:22.640
of your interests, a rigidly

01:08:22.760 --> 01:08:24.040
circumscribed sphere of your

01:08:24.040 --> 01:08:25.480
enterprise, where you work

01:08:25.480 --> 01:08:27.600
and where you do things.

01:08:29.160 --> 01:08:31.840
Naturally, this model of

01:08:31.840 --> 01:08:33.700
gradational behavior was very rigid

01:08:33.700 --> 01:08:36.940
and did not allow for any backlash

01:08:36.940 --> 01:08:39.540
from the executive.

01:08:40.280 --> 01:08:42.120
There are instructions, there is work.

01:08:42.940 --> 01:08:44.560
As far as the managers were concerned,

01:08:44.680 --> 01:08:46.360
there was also a rigid hierarchy,

01:08:46.360 --> 01:08:48.080
and this rigid hierarchy led to

01:08:48.080 --> 01:08:49.840
the fact that everyone knew what

01:08:49.840 --> 01:08:52.800
to do, and everyone knew what he

01:08:52.800 --> 01:08:54.920
was responsible for.

01:08:55.380 --> 01:08:57.700
It was always possible to identify

01:08:57.700 --> 01:08:59.360
at what element and at what stage a

01:08:59.360 --> 01:09:01.180
failure occurred, and to find the culprit,

01:09:01.240 --> 01:09:03.020
who could be punished.

01:09:03.680 --> 01:09:07.480
This rigid hierarchy, it introduced

01:09:07.480 --> 01:09:10.660
the function that professionals

01:09:11.200 --> 01:09:14.200
had to work in every field,

01:09:14.200 --> 01:09:16.520
and it was always possible to find

01:09:16.520 --> 01:09:18.980
out who made the mistake that caused

01:09:19.860 --> 01:09:24.040
the defect in the overall work.

01:09:25.960 --> 01:09:28.660
In principle, as far as this

01:09:28.660 --> 01:09:31.880
model is concerned, this model

01:09:31.880 --> 01:09:33.960
of research existed somewhere,

01:09:34.440 --> 01:09:37.580
well, perhaps until

01:09:37.580 --> 01:09:38.980
the 1920s.

01:09:41.080 --> 01:09:44.360
And it was only in the 1920s that

01:09:44.360 --> 01:09:50.080
this model became necessary, not even

01:09:50.080 --> 01:09:50.720
in the sense that it was

01:09:50.720 --> 01:09:53.440
necessary, but it became clear

01:09:53.440 --> 01:09:57.080
that this model had exhausted itself.

01:09:57.800 --> 01:09:59.860
Naturally, to a great extent this

01:09:59.860 --> 01:10:02.280
happened due to the fact that production

01:10:02.280 --> 01:10:04.720
was developing, science

01:10:04.980 --> 01:10:06.940
was developing, new equipment

01:10:06.940 --> 01:10:08.660
was appearing, new machines

01:10:08.660 --> 01:10:10.400
were appearing, new aggregates

01:10:10.400 --> 01:10:14.040
were appearing, and more and

01:10:14.040 --> 01:10:16.820
more workers were stuck to

01:10:16.820 --> 01:10:18.160
maintaining one machine.

01:10:18.560 --> 01:10:21.040
So the problem was that

01:10:21.040 --> 01:10:23.140
this maintenance required

01:10:23.140 --> 01:10:25.500
a lot of initiative.

01:10:25.500 --> 01:10:27.140


01:10:27.380 --> 01:10:29.140
And it was initiative that would

01:10:29.140 --> 01:10:31.120
not be rigidly declared, simply

01:10:32.040 --> 01:10:35.020
because sometimes a worker with

01:10:35.380 --> 01:10:37.220
extensive experience on certain

01:10:37.220 --> 01:10:38.800
kinds of machines might be

01:10:38.800 --> 01:10:40.760
more competent than the

01:10:40.760 --> 01:10:41.980
supervisor above him, who

01:10:41.980 --> 01:10:43.960
was giving him instructions.

01:10:44.240 --> 01:10:45.400
The worker might know that if a

01:10:45.400 --> 01:10:47.640
given machine worked at the same

01:10:47.640 --> 01:10:48.840
load, at the same speed, then after

01:10:48.840 --> 01:10:51.440
a while the cutter would go bad, the

01:10:51.440 --> 01:10:54.820
chisel would break or the worker

01:10:54.820 --> 01:10:56.600
knew this from his own experience,

01:10:56.600 --> 01:10:59.240
but of course nobody listened to

01:10:59.240 --> 01:11:00.580
him simply because he was the

01:11:00.580 --> 01:11:03.000
worker and it was the supervisor.

01:11:03.680 --> 01:11:04.580
As the equipment became more and

01:11:04.580 --> 01:11:06.020
more complex, as more and more

01:11:06.020 --> 01:11:07.200
new equipment appeared, as more

01:11:07.200 --> 01:11:09.120
and more new connections emerged,

01:11:09.120 --> 01:11:10.840
as industry developed, as industry

01:11:10.840 --> 01:11:11.980
developed, the problem

01:11:11.980 --> 01:11:15.760
