01:17:08.580 --> 01:17:10.220
it is, girls' sleeping hours, how

01:17:10.220 --> 01:17:12.280
much they sleep, and how much

01:17:12.280 --> 01:17:15.040
of this sleeping time is

01:17:15.040 --> 01:17:18.380
significant in terms of mistakes,

01:17:18.380 --> 01:17:22.760
in terms of marriage.

01:17:23.380 --> 01:17:25.620
How much time do girls have to work

01:17:25.620 --> 01:17:27.200
so that marriage doesn't show up?

01:17:27.320 --> 01:17:31.060
How often do they need to take these or

01:17:31.060 --> 01:17:33.980
those breaks?

01:17:33.980 --> 01:17:36.260
Naturally, initially Rhett Lisberger,

01:17:36.260 --> 01:17:39.560
May Dixon, they went in the

01:17:39.560 --> 01:17:41.720
vein of Taylor and just did

01:17:41.720 --> 01:17:44.140
timing, made instruction

01:17:44.140 --> 01:17:45.360
cards, enumerated

01:17:45.560 --> 01:17:46.860
operations, engaged

01:17:47.280 --> 01:17:50.000
in teaching girls behavior.

01:17:50.680 --> 01:17:52.920
And then they began to analyze the

01:17:52.920 --> 01:17:57.280
external conditions of work, what

01:17:57.280 --> 01:18:00.440
a little later Heisberger would

01:18:00.440 --> 01:18:01.940
call the hygienic factors of work.

01:18:03.760 --> 01:18:06.120
They were interested in what the

01:18:06.120 --> 01:18:08.380
lighting should be, what the noise

01:18:08.380 --> 01:18:11.400
level should be, what kind of

01:18:11.400 --> 01:18:13.140
room the girls should be in,

01:18:13.140 --> 01:18:14.760
how far apart they should sit,

01:18:14.760 --> 01:18:17.240
how far they should stretch

01:18:17.240 --> 01:18:22.780
to get the finished piece, how

01:18:22.780 --> 01:18:24.680
tired they were from this, and

01:18:24.680 --> 01:18:25.040
so on.

01:18:26.880 --> 01:18:29.240
We studied lighting conditions,

01:18:30.280 --> 01:18:33.560
time-work conditions,

01:18:34.440 --> 01:18:40.260
lunch-break conditions,

01:18:40.260 --> 01:18:42.780
time conditions, how long

01:18:42.780 --> 01:18:43.960
it took to pick up

01:18:43.960 --> 01:18:46.460
a tool, pick up a part,

01:18:46.460 --> 01:18:47.380
and so on.

01:18:50.280 --> 01:18:52.660
Accordingly, it was these external

01:18:52.660 --> 01:18:56.620
factors that were changing, and

01:18:56.620 --> 01:18:58.940
Mayo and the authors noticed

01:18:58.940 --> 01:19:02.020
that some change corresponded

01:19:02.020 --> 01:19:04.560
to an increase in productivity,

01:19:04.760 --> 01:19:06.960
some worsened it.

01:19:07.520 --> 01:19:09.060
These were factors related to

01:19:09.060 --> 01:19:11.160
production, what Taylor was doing.

01:19:11.520 --> 01:19:15.520
And then Rettlisberger, Mayo, and

01:19:15.520 --> 01:19:18.960
Dixon decided to introduce these very

01:19:18.960 --> 01:19:20.680
social elements.

01:19:22.380 --> 01:19:26.420
The girls began to receive meals from the

01:19:26.420 --> 01:19:27.460
factory, that is, they no longer

01:19:27.460 --> 01:19:29.520
brought food with them as they had

01:19:29.520 --> 01:19:30.000
done before.

01:19:30.580 --> 01:19:32.720
They started getting hot

01:19:32.720 --> 01:19:34.920
meals, hot lunches.

01:19:35.260 --> 01:19:37.460
During the breaks they received buns,

01:19:37.940 --> 01:19:39.480
milk, something else.

01:19:40.640 --> 01:19:42.720
And they did not get it at their own expense,

01:19:42.720 --> 01:19:44.700
it was at the employer's expense.

01:19:48.780 --> 01:19:50.660
Accordingly, if a girl was

01:19:50.660 --> 01:19:52.640
tired, she could interrupt her work,

01:19:52.640 --> 01:19:54.820
rest, not according to the

01:19:54.820 --> 01:19:57.080
time you were supposed

01:19:57.080 --> 01:19:59.320
to, for example, two hours of

01:19:59.320 --> 01:20:00.920
work, 10 minutes to rest.

01:20:01.180 --> 01:20:02.480
Here you feel like you're tired now.

01:20:02.860 --> 01:20:04.680
You interrupt, have a little

01:20:04.680 --> 01:20:06.180
rest, and then continue your

01:20:06.180 --> 01:20:06.780
work.

01:20:07.120 --> 01:20:09.860
That is, gradually, they allowed the

01:20:09.860 --> 01:20:12.440
subjective needs of the girls to manifest

01:20:12.440 --> 01:20:14.640
themselves, that is, they themselves

01:20:14.640 --> 01:20:17.320
regulate these or other conditions

01:20:17.320 --> 01:20:18.220
of work.

01:20:19.380 --> 01:20:21.780
And the researchers noticed that

01:20:22.500 --> 01:20:25.320
productivity has increased

01:20:25.320 --> 01:20:26.560
dramatically.

01:20:26.940 --> 01:20:28.060
The researchers conducted everything

01:20:28.060 --> 01:20:28.720
as it should be.

01:20:28.820 --> 01:20:30.240
There was a group of girls

01:20:30.240 --> 01:20:31.560
or an experimental group they

01:20:31.560 --> 01:20:32.300
worked on.

01:20:32.620 --> 01:20:34.280
There was a control group that was

01:20:34.280 --> 01:20:36.300
working under normal conditions

01:20:36.300 --> 01:20:37.740
for that Western Digital plant, assembling

01:20:37.820 --> 01:20:39.240
the same relays.

01:20:40.660 --> 01:20:42.440
And naturally, the researchers

01:20:42.440 --> 01:20:44.700
noticed that productivity began

01:20:44.700 --> 01:20:46.760
to increase dramatically.

01:20:47.280 --> 01:20:48.440
It was a dramatic increase.

01:20:50.320 --> 01:20:52.460
Naturally, this was reflected,

01:20:52.580 --> 01:20:53.620
especially, again, note, these

01:20:53.620 --> 01:20:54.980
experiments lasted 5 years,

01:20:54.980 --> 01:20:57.320
and as for those 5 years, it

01:20:57.320 --> 01:20:58.920
was quite a difficult time

01:20:58.920 --> 01:21:01.760
for America, it was the

01:21:01.760 --> 01:21:04.480
time of the Great Depression.

01:21:04.800 --> 01:21:07.560
And yet, all the same, money was given

01:21:07.560 --> 01:21:09.020
to Litwinningram and her to

01:21:10.720 --> 01:21:14.020
allocate the experiments.

01:21:14.980 --> 01:21:18.120
So, the researchers noticed,

01:21:18.360 --> 01:21:20.220
productivity, the more attentive

01:21:20.220 --> 01:21:24.260
you were to the female workers,

01:21:24.260 --> 01:21:26.720
the more interested you were

01:21:26.720 --> 01:21:28.280
in their work, their

01:21:28.400 --> 01:21:29.980
productivity increased.

01:21:30.560 --> 01:21:36.140
And then the researchers, after looking

01:21:36.260 --> 01:21:40.020
at ways to increase labor productivity,

01:21:40.020 --> 01:21:42.420
asked themselves a second question.

01:21:42.820 --> 01:21:45.140
Now how do we reduce these

01:21:45.140 --> 01:21:45.900
costs?

01:21:46.360 --> 01:21:49.460
And they started slowly depriving the

01:21:49.460 --> 01:21:51.140
girls of what they were used to.

01:21:51.800 --> 01:22:00.900
Lunch, buns, reduced rest time,

01:22:00.900 --> 01:22:05.300
reduced lighting conditions,

01:22:05.300 --> 01:22:08.060
increased the noise conditions,

01:22:08.060 --> 01:22:12.100
because, of course, it

01:22:12.100 --> 01:22:14.020
was a specific task, set

01:22:14.020 --> 01:22:15.520
by the owners, to find

01:22:15.520 --> 01:22:17.640
the best conditions.

01:22:17.720 --> 01:22:18.600
That's what they were doing.

01:22:18.640 --> 01:22:21.720
And here the most interesting

01:22:21.720 --> 01:22:23.060
paradox happened.

01:22:23.820 --> 01:22:25.660
The girls who were, shall we say, used

01:22:25.720 --> 01:22:27.360
to paradisiacal working conditions.

01:22:27.440 --> 01:22:29.160
They were paradisiacal compared

01:22:29.160 --> 01:22:31.020
to how other female workers in the

01:22:31.020 --> 01:22:32.480
same factory worked.

01:22:33.280 --> 01:22:35.960
After all these conditions

01:22:35.960 --> 01:22:37.220
began to be abolished,

01:22:37.840 --> 01:22:39.000
labor productivity

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:40.920
hardly dropped.

01:22:41.540 --> 01:22:44.020
Now this was a completely incomprehensible thing.

01:22:44.020 --> 01:22:45.940
It went completely against

01:22:45.940 --> 01:22:48.720
the classics, the same Taylor

01:22:48.720 --> 01:22:52.940
Fayolly had a huge amount

01:22:52.940 --> 01:22:54.240
of evidence that if I change

01:22:54.240 --> 01:22:56.460
the working conditions,

01:22:56.460 --> 01:22:58.360
it affects productivity.

01:22:59.580 --> 01:23:02.980
There was a clear deterioration

01:23:02.980 --> 01:23:04.920
in working conditions,

01:23:05.320 --> 01:23:07.960
and yet productivity hardly dropped.

01:23:08.620 --> 01:23:11.940
Moreover, well, let's just say, maybe

01:23:11.940 --> 01:23:14.480
from an ethical point of view, those

01:23:14.480 --> 01:23:16.180
experiments that Red Lisbergellar, Mayo

01:23:16.180 --> 01:23:19.480
Dixon produced would be criticized

01:23:19.480 --> 01:23:22.340
now because they were, I should say,

01:23:22.340 --> 01:23:23.640
so unethical, but let's just

01:23:23.640 --> 01:23:25.540
say that first the girls are promoted

01:23:25.540 --> 01:23:27.920
to good things and then they

01:23:27.920 --> 01:23:29.060
start depriving them of that.

01:23:30.800 --> 01:23:34.520
But then Mayo did get

01:23:34.520 --> 01:23:37.260
interested, and until when can I

01:23:37.260 --> 01:23:39.080
worsen these conditions of

01:23:39.080 --> 01:23:41.540
labor so that the productivity

01:23:41.540 --> 01:23:43.080
of labor It does fall, because

01:23:43.080 --> 01:23:43.980
he got interested again.

01:23:44.380 --> 01:23:45.700
According to the classical model, they

01:23:45.700 --> 01:23:47.000
should be falling, but they're not.

01:23:48.440 --> 01:23:50.300
He had already started to make them significantly worse.

01:23:50.520 --> 01:23:52.600
The girls were working almost in semi-darkness.

01:23:52.720 --> 01:23:53.640
Naturally, this had a negative

01:23:53.640 --> 01:23:55.360
effect on their vision.

01:23:55.920 --> 01:23:58.840
It was going down, but her productivity

01:23:58.840 --> 01:24:01.560
was not going down significantly.

01:24:01.860 --> 01:24:04.220
She was in this group of girls who

01:24:04.480 --> 01:24:05.960
were already working in conditions

01:24:05.960 --> 01:24:08.700
worse than other workers in the

01:24:08.700 --> 01:24:10.120
factory, almost in semi-darkness.

01:24:10.120 --> 01:24:12.100
Naturally, this was not the case in the factory.

01:24:12.820 --> 01:24:14.460
The productivity of this

01:24:14.460 --> 01:24:16.780
group was still higher than

01:24:16.780 --> 01:24:18.820
that of the girls in the

01:24:18.820 --> 01:24:20.660
control group.

01:24:20.860 --> 01:24:24.560
Well, naturally, the researchers were interested.

01:24:24.720 --> 01:24:25.520
So what's going on?

01:24:26.080 --> 01:24:27.260
They were interested in everything

01:24:27.260 --> 01:24:28.660
naturally from a scientific point of view.

01:24:28.960 --> 01:24:30.820
After all, this was a refutation

01:24:30.820 --> 01:24:32.880
of the paradigm, the paradigm of classical

01:24:32.880 --> 01:24:33.800
labor organization.

01:24:34.160 --> 01:24:35.760
And these were facts from which there

01:24:35.760 --> 01:24:36.720
was no escaping.

01:24:37.660 --> 01:24:39.180
The girls who were used to working

01:24:39.180 --> 01:24:40.960
in semi-darkness, who were used to working

01:24:40.960 --> 01:24:44.360
in perfect light, noise was added, other

01:24:44.360 --> 01:24:45.700
disturbances were added.

01:24:46.020 --> 01:24:47.140
Work productivity was still

01:24:47.140 --> 01:24:47.600
higher.

01:24:47.720 --> 01:24:49.620
Yes, it certainly dropped

01:24:49.620 --> 01:24:52.840
compared to what these same girls

01:24:52.840 --> 01:24:53.620
had before.

01:24:53.880 --> 01:24:56.960
But it still didn't drop

01:24:56.960 --> 01:24:58.760
so much that the girls could

01:24:58.760 --> 01:25:01.720
be fired and therefore

01:25:02.240 --> 01:25:03.780
recruited.

01:25:07.640 --> 01:25:11.520
Rrth Lisberger, Mayu Dixon,

01:25:11.520 --> 01:25:12.620
and the others next I worked

01:25:12.620 --> 01:25:14.040
with wondered what the

01:25:14.040 --> 01:25:15.460
reason was.

01:25:16.640 --> 01:25:18.020
Naturally, they were interested in this

01:25:18.020 --> 01:25:20.720
from a scientific point of view, and it

01:25:20.720 --> 01:25:22.660
was then that they turned their

01:25:22.660 --> 01:25:26.920
attention to what might be keeping

01:25:26.920 --> 01:25:29.840
the girls in these already hellish

01:25:29.840 --> 01:25:31.280
working conditions.

01:25:31.700 --> 01:25:34.600
And, since Mayo and Dixon were

01:25:34.600 --> 01:25:36.640
psychologists, they suddenly

01:25:36.640 --> 01:25:39.320
noticed that girls tend

01:25:39.320 --> 01:25:42.440
to stick together, they

01:25:42.440 --> 01:25:45.380
are interested in being

01:25:45.380 --> 01:25:46.640
with each other.

01:25:47.040 --> 01:25:50.120
Yes, and working conditions worsened,

01:25:50.240 --> 01:25:52.700
yes, the lighting worsened, but

01:25:52.700 --> 01:25:54.520
it was interesting for them to

01:25:54.520 --> 01:25:56.320
talk to each other during this work,

01:25:56.320 --> 01:25:58.300
it was interesting for them to

01:25:58.300 --> 01:26:02.220
criticize and scold these bad

01:26:02.220 --> 01:26:05.820
researchers, because of whom

01:26:05.820 --> 01:26:07.180
we lose our eyesight.

01:26:07.700 --> 01:26:09.340
They had an inner understanding,

01:26:09.340 --> 01:26:11.360
an inner unity.

01:26:11.680 --> 01:26:13.760
They formed a kind of

01:26:13.760 --> 01:26:16.020
close-knit group.

01:26:17.800 --> 01:26:20.620
This situation was completely unexpected

01:26:20.620 --> 01:26:22.320
and ran completely counter to the

01:26:22.320 --> 01:26:22.940
classics.

01:26:23.420 --> 01:26:25.460
It turned out that all these external conditions,

01:26:25.460 --> 01:26:28.760
of course, they are important, but, nevertheless,

01:26:29.020 --> 01:26:31.040
they are not the only ones.

01:26:31.480 --> 01:26:34.080
In addition to them, there is another factor.

01:26:34.400 --> 01:26:37.740
The factor of human relations,

01:26:37.740 --> 01:26:39.160
or this informal attitude.

01:26:39.700 --> 01:26:40.660
These are all the things we talked

01:26:40.660 --> 01:26:41.980
about, about the ethics of relations in

01:26:41.980 --> 01:26:43.720
the beginning, about the culture of relations.

01:26:44.400 --> 01:26:46.420
And this factor, this factor

01:26:46.420 --> 01:26:48.220
of informal relations that exist

01:26:48.220 --> 01:26:49.600
within the group is so

01:26:50.340 --> 01:26:52.500
important and so strong that

01:26:52.880 --> 01:26:56.480
it is able to suppress all

01:26:56.480 --> 01:27:00.680
external objective negatives.

01:27:02.540 --> 01:27:05.820
And we based it on... What

01:27:05.820 --> 01:27:06.660
concerns the Hutter

01:27:06.660 --> 01:27:09.260
experiments, a great number

01:27:09.260 --> 01:27:12.180
of results were formed on their basis.

01:27:12.720 --> 01:27:14.540
They gave rise to the development

01:27:14.540 --> 01:27:16.280
of all of social psychology,

01:27:16.280 --> 01:27:17.660
all of industrial-organizational

01:27:17.660 --> 01:27:19.040
psychology, all of those

01:27:19.040 --> 01:27:21.520
very disciplines that

01:27:21.520 --> 01:27:22.560
we spoke about at the

01:27:22.560 --> 01:27:23.660
very beginning.

01:27:24.980 --> 01:27:26.720
It was Mayo who formulated the

01:27:26.720 --> 01:27:28.340
doctrine of human relations on the

01:27:28.340 --> 01:27:30.540
basis of these experiments.

01:27:31.160 --> 01:27:33.340
He was the first to formulate this

01:27:33.340 --> 01:27:34.860
doctrine in management, in

01:27:34.860 --> 01:27:36.000
the manager as such.

01:27:37.880 --> 01:27:40.460
What Mayo did was to point

01:27:40.460 --> 01:27:43.520
out that in addition to all

01:27:43.520 --> 01:27:47.380
those points that are very

01:27:47.460 --> 01:27:48.780
well covered in the classical

01:27:48.780 --> 01:27:50.560
model, we should also consider

01:27:51.320 --> 01:27:53.800
such an element as these

01:27:53.800 --> 01:27:56.240
subjective human essence,

01:27:56.240 --> 01:27:58.260
these human relations.

01:27:58.260 --> 01:27:59.600


01:27:59.900 --> 01:28:01.980
Because these human relations

01:28:01.980 --> 01:28:04.180
have no less of an influence

01:28:04.180 --> 01:28:07.140
on the result of production

01:28:07.140 --> 01:28:09.900
than all the objective factors.

01:28:13.300 --> 01:28:15.200
What concerns the doctrine of

01:28:15.200 --> 01:28:16.600
human relations, at first it was not

01:28:16.600 --> 01:28:18.880
accepted, a lot of business owners

01:28:18.880 --> 01:28:20.780
were against it, because they

01:28:20.780 --> 01:28:24.460
thought it was just another blasphemy

01:28:24.460 --> 01:28:27.200
of scientists, whose goal was to

01:28:27.200 --> 01:28:30.340
conduct this or that research, and,

01:28:30.340 --> 01:28:32.500
accordingly, they were not

01:28:32.780 --> 01:28:37.240
interested in commerce itself,

01:28:37.240 --> 01:28:39.080
they were interested in their own

01:28:39.080 --> 01:28:39.920
interests.

01:28:40.280 --> 01:28:44.460
But what concerns Majori, Lisberg,

01:28:44.480 --> 01:28:46.620
Dixon, their followers,

01:28:46.620 --> 01:28:49.020
their collaborators, they showed

01:28:49.020 --> 01:28:51.940
that it is possible to treat their

01:28:51.940 --> 01:28:54.680
ideas, these informal relations,

01:28:54.680 --> 01:28:56.500
and the doctrine of human relations

01:28:56.500 --> 01:28:58.080
itself in different ways.

01:28:58.520 --> 01:29:01.380
However, if you take it into account,

01:29:01.380 --> 01:29:03.880
there is a sharp increase

01:29:03.880 --> 01:29:05.260
in labor productivity.

01:29:05.860 --> 01:29:07.360
This has been proven

01:29:07.360 --> 01:29:09.320
experimentally, and there is no getting

01:29:09.320 --> 01:29:10.260
away from it.

01:29:10.920 --> 01:29:13.000
As far as businessmen are concerned,

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:15.100
they are people of facts, and

01:29:15.100 --> 01:29:16.820
when they are shown the facts, they

01:29:17.100 --> 01:29:18.560
accept them.

01:29:19.260 --> 01:29:20.520
What is the doctrine

01:29:20.520 --> 01:29:22.620
of human relations, as it

01:29:22.620 --> 01:29:24.100
was formulated by mine, as

01:29:24.100 --> 01:29:25.100
it was formulated by

01:29:26.520 --> 01:29:30.440
my followers, and, accordingly,

01:29:30.560 --> 01:29:31.580
as it is formulated

01:29:31.580 --> 01:29:32.860
now.

01:29:34.620 --> 01:29:36.700
The main fact is that man

01:29:36.780 --> 01:29:40.420
is a full-fledged and equally

01:29:40.420 --> 01:29:43.680
important element of production.

01:29:44.520 --> 01:29:46.640
And if we want to understand, to

01:29:46.820 --> 01:29:50.300
understand why production functions

01:29:50.300 --> 01:29:52.380
successfully or unsuccessfully, why

01:29:52.480 --> 01:29:53.980
we are either ahead of our

01:29:53.980 --> 01:29:55.580
competitors or not ahead of them,

01:29:56.020 --> 01:29:58.080
we must take this very human factor

01:29:58.080 --> 01:29:59.480
into account.

01:29:59.760 --> 01:30:00.720
There is a lot of talk about

01:30:00.720 --> 01:30:03.020
this now, but the very notion

01:30:03.020 --> 01:30:04.480
of the human factor, in fact, was

01:30:04.600 --> 01:30:06.800
introduced by her inspiration

01:30:06.800 --> 01:30:07.900
of human relations.

01:30:09.200 --> 01:30:11.820
It came from the fact

01:30:11.820 --> 01:30:14.560
that man is a social being.

01:30:15.080 --> 01:30:16.620
Again, this was obvious to

01:30:16.620 --> 01:30:18.520
him, being a psychologist, he

01:30:18.760 --> 01:30:20.400
naturally knew this.

01:30:20.700 --> 01:30:22.660
But the important thing was that

01:30:22.660 --> 01:30:24.440
as a social being, man is oriented

01:30:24.780 --> 01:30:27.020
toward other people, and his organizational

01:30:27.020 --> 01:30:30.080
behavior, that is, his work,

01:30:30.080 --> 01:30:32.640
his behavior in the organization,

01:30:32.640 --> 01:30:36.460
is included in the context

01:30:36.460 --> 01:30:38.460
of group behavior.

01:30:39.020 --> 01:30:41.220
If we want to understand how a person

01:30:41.220 --> 01:30:43.160
works, we must first of all study

01:30:43.160 --> 01:30:45.920
the group of people in which he

01:30:45.920 --> 01:30:46.860
is located.

01:30:47.880 --> 01:30:50.200
This is the group

01:30:50.200 --> 01:30:52.380
of his immediate environment or the

01:30:52.380 --> 01:30:53.780
primary group.

01:30:54.700 --> 01:30:57.100
After her, the massive study

01:30:57.100 --> 01:30:58.660
of primary groups began.

01:30:59.240 --> 01:31:00.640
There are many researchers here,

01:31:00.900 --> 01:31:03.280
for example, Charles Cooley, other authors.

01:31:03.760 --> 01:31:06.580
But the main factor from our point of

01:31:06.580 --> 01:31:07.660
view, from the point of view of the

01:31:07.660 --> 01:31:10.020
pattern of behavior, was that a person's

01:31:10.020 --> 01:31:11.660
behavior in an organization

01:31:11.660 --> 01:31:15.420
is not determined by his individual

01:31:15.420 --> 01:31:17.180
psychological characteristics alone,

01:31:17.180 --> 01:31:19.360
but is determined by the behavior

01:31:19.360 --> 01:31:21.440
of the group in which he is

01:31:21.440 --> 01:31:22.340
included.

01:31:23.140 --> 01:31:24.580
We have drawn attention to the fact that

01:31:24.580 --> 01:31:27.100
the behavior of the individual as such and the

01:31:27.100 --> 01:31:29.200
behavior of the individual in the group are

01:31:29.200 --> 01:31:31.000
two great differences, as they are called.

01:31:31.000 --> 01:31:32.580
And, therefore, if we are looking

01:31:32.580 --> 01:31:33.500
at organizational behavior, which

01:31:33.500 --> 01:31:35.620
is the behavior of large groups

01:31:35.620 --> 01:31:37.140
of people engaged in an organization,

01:31:37.240 --> 01:31:39.820
then we need to study not only

01:31:39.820 --> 01:31:42.480
and not so much the behavior

01:31:42.480 --> 01:31:44.360
of a single person, what Taylor

01:31:44.560 --> 01:31:46.420
was doing, in fact, what

01:31:46.540 --> 01:31:48.460
Fayol was talking about.

01:31:48.760 --> 01:31:50.180
We must first look at group behavior,

01:31:50.180 --> 01:31:52.460
group norms, group values, and it

01:31:52.580 --> 01:31:55.060
is these group norms and values,

01:31:55.060 --> 01:31:56.580
they are precisely then that

01:31:56.580 --> 01:31:59.340
will be accepted by the individual,

01:32:00.180 --> 01:32:02.240
perceived, and will be realized

01:32:02.240 --> 01:32:03.480
by his behavior.

01:32:04.140 --> 01:32:06.960
Not his norms and values, which is very

01:32:06.960 --> 01:32:09.020
important, but the group norms and values.

01:32:09.380 --> 01:32:11.160
The correlation of individual

01:32:11.160 --> 01:32:12.220
norms and group values

01:32:12.220 --> 01:32:13.580
is a separate problem that

01:32:13.580 --> 01:32:15.100
exists in social psychology.

01:32:16.060 --> 01:32:17.520
Many regularities have

01:32:17.520 --> 01:32:18.800
been found out there, and, naturally,

01:32:18.920 --> 01:32:20.260
the theory of organizational behavior

01:32:20.260 --> 01:32:22.920
studies and takes these regularities.

01:32:23.080 --> 01:32:25.720
This is the area that is taken

01:32:25.900 --> 01:32:27.240
from social psychology in

01:32:27.420 --> 01:32:29.600
the theory of aggressive behavior.

01:32:30.420 --> 01:32:33.960
But this is the first and important

01:32:34.640 --> 01:32:36.760
aspect when the emphasis is placed

01:32:36.760 --> 01:32:37.960
first on human relations,

01:32:38.080 --> 01:32:39.540
the human factor, and then on the

01:32:39.540 --> 01:32:40.500
group factor.

01:32:41.560 --> 01:32:44.360
The next thing that Mayow drew attention

01:32:44.360 --> 01:32:46.040
to with his doctrine of human relations

01:32:46.040 --> 01:32:48.280
is that, and this again was obtained

01:32:48.780 --> 01:32:51.220
experimentally during his

01:32:51.220 --> 01:32:52.860
Hatong experiments, human nature

01:32:52.860 --> 01:32:54.360
appears to be incompatible

01:32:55.120 --> 01:32:57.500
with the rigid hierarchy

01:32:57.500 --> 01:33:01.000
and bureaucracy of subordination

01:33:01.000 --> 01:33:03.260
that is found in organizations.

01:33:03.260 --> 01:33:04.440


01:33:06.400 --> 01:33:10.260
Man can be forced to perform

01:33:10.260 --> 01:33:12.020
certain actions,

01:33:12.220 --> 01:33:16.360
certain factors, but he

01:33:16.360 --> 01:33:19.220
will tend not to do them,

01:33:19.220 --> 01:33:21.120
and he will consciously

01:33:21.120 --> 01:33:24.060
sabotage certain actions,

01:33:24.060 --> 01:33:27.640
which will manifest

01:33:27.640 --> 01:33:30.660
itself in marriage, affecting

01:33:31.020 --> 01:33:33.300
labor productivity and

01:33:33.300 --> 01:33:35.200
the effects that arise

01:33:35.300 --> 01:33:36.400
here.
